  "market_context": "Tuesday session on ETH following a top-down framing exercise. Previous day high was marked as the drawn liquidity target. Price action during Asia session was monitored to assess whether PDH would remain a valid target for London/New York sessions.",
  "key_observation": "Asia session already took out the previous day high, removing the drawn liquidity target. With PDH already swept, there was no remaining draw to frame a New York session entry, so the analyst chose to stand aside.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Marked out the previous day high on the lower time frames to frame drawn liquidity for the new day.",
    "Step 2: Observed price action during Asia session and noted that PDH was already taken out during Asia.",
    "Step 3: Concluded that with the drawn liquidity already achieved in Asia, there was no valid target framing for the New York session.",
    "Step 4: Decided to pass on the New York session and let price play out to confirm — observed continuation of order flow higher into New York AM session."
  ],
  "outcome": "No trade taken; price continued higher into New York AM session as a continuation of order flow after PDH had already been swept in Asia.",
  "lessons": "When the drawn liquidity (PDH/PDL) is already taken during Asia session, the primary directional target for the day's later sessions is removed. Without a clear draw on liquidity to frame the trade, it is best to stand aside rather than force a setup.",
